\"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"unforgettable experiences\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"meticulously trained athletes\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 865}, {\"ngram\": \"a mountainous plateau\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"the eastern Korean Peninsula\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have been through a lot so that we could blaze a trail,\\\" said Kim Eun-jung, skip of the South Korean women's curling team, which captured global renown as the \\\"Garlic Girls\\\" - all from a garlic-producing Korean hometown.\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Eun-jung_(curler)\", \"score\": 0.98400824585817, \"rank\": 0.012917563719702584, \"text\": \"Kim Eun-jung\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Eun-jung_(curler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Eun-jung_(curler)\"}, {\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9998393533717302, \"rank\": 0.0001606646213734509, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9998393533717302, \"rank\": 0.0001606646213734509, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1055}, {\"ngram\": \"a trail\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1086}, {\"ngram\": \"skip\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1112}, {\"ngram\": \"global renown\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Garlic Girls\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They made a good run for gold before finishing with runner-up silver.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1322, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good run\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1282}, {\"ngram\": \"runner-up silver\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1321}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the sun set on the games' final day, people began trickling into Olympic Stadium to encounter a far different atmosphere that showed one of the games' memorable arcs: the weather.\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1506, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sun\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1334}, {\"ngram\": \"the games' final day\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1362}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1370}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Stadium\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"a far different atmosphere\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1447}, {\"ngram\": \"the games' memorable arcs\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"the weather\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Temperatures, so bitterly frigid at the outset that some spectators had to take cover from opening-ceremony winds, were nearly 20 degrees warmer (11 degrees Celsius) as the evening began.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1694, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Temperatures\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1519}, {\"ngram\": \"the outset\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1553}, {\"ngram\": \"some spectators\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"cover\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"opening-ceremony winds\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1620}, {\"ngram\": \"Celsius\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"the evening\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other trailblazers: Chloe Kim, American snowboarder extraordinaire.\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chloe Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\"}, {\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.115082167671985e-17, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other trailblazers\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. women's hockey team and men's curlers, both of which claimed gold.\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1839, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The U.S. women's hockey team\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1792}, {\"ngram\": \"men's curlers\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1838}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Russian hockey team, with its nail-biting, overtime victory against Germany.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1848, \"end\": 1855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999440751723, \"rank\": 3.986735498716577e-08, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.8005459284798448, \"rank\": 0.23589067757827745, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its nail-biting, overtime victory\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1907}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That these games would be circumscribed by politics was a given from the outset because of regional rivalries.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 2036, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these games\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1977}, {\"ngram\": \"the outset\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"regional rivalries\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"North Korea, South Korea, Japan and China are neighbors with deep, sometimes twisted histories that get along uneasily with each other in this particular geographic cul-de-sac.\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6244145296343358e-23, \"text\": \"North Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2050, \"end\": 2061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1596937405634255e-22, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2063, \"end\": 2068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9962765811879793, \"rank\": 0.0037373342548016977, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 2073, \"end\": 2078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999998153726, \"rank\": 1.8373254117817905e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"neighbors\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2092}, {\"ngram\": \"deep, sometimes twisted histories\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2131}, {\"ngram\": \"this particular geographic cul\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"de\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"sac\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there was something more this time around.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2238}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hanging over the entire games was the saga - or opportunity, if you prefer - of a delicate diplomatic dance between the Koreas, North and South, riven by war and discord and an armed border for the better part of a century.\", \"from\": 2262, \"to\": 2485, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the entire games\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"the saga\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2304}, {\"ngram\": \"opportunity\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"a delicate diplomatic dance\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2369}, {\"ngram\": \"the Koreas\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2388}, {\"ngram\": \"North\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2395}, {\"ngram\": \"South\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2405}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2419}, {\"ngram\": \"discord\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"an armed border\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"the better part\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2471}, {\"ngram\": \"a century\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2484}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The games started with a last-minute flurry of agreements to bring North Koreans to South Korea to compete under one combined Koreas banner.\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2560, \"end\": 2567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koreans\", \"score\": 0.9999978420760818, \"rank\": 2.15753647589655e-06, \"text\": \"Koreans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koreans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koreans\"}, {\"begin\": 2571, \"end\": 2582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1596937405634255e-22, \"text\": \"South 